The new species is distinguished from
Astyanax leonidas Azpelicueta, Casciotta & Almiron
;
A. ojiara Azpelicueta & Garcia
;
A. troya Azpelicueta, Casciotta & Almiron
;
A. pynandi Casciotta, Almiron & Azpelicueta
;
A. chico Casciotta & Almiron
;
A. hermosus Miquelarena, Protogino & Lopez
; and A. tumbayaensis Miquelarena & Menni by the absence of hooks on the dorsal, caudal and/or pectoral fins of males. Astyanax endy differs from A. ojiara , A. troya , A. pynandi , A. chico , and
A. ita Almiron , Azpelicueta & Casciotta
in having 4 gradually decreasing dentary teeth, 1 intermediate, and 4-7 posterior conical teeth of approximately equal size (vs. 7-10 gradually decreasing dentary teeth).
